0.1.3
    - Fixed ARP lookup for Linux
    - Fixed i18n for Linux

0.1.2
    - Reverted back to old style defined-or operator since perl <5.9.0 does not support C-style //
    - Reverted back to old style $p->{port_num} since Net::Ping <2.33 does not support method port_number()
    * Switched to DB_File from AnyDBM_File for identical behavior at different OSes
    - Fixed HTTP and HTML headers (expires and lang parameters)
    * Now if the remote host replies ECONNREFUSED, it is considered unreachable (important for routed networks)

0.1.1
    - Fixed HTML markup
    + Added "Backup Database" button
